/www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p class=\"button-wrapper\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://framer.link/NEWECONOMIES&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Apply Now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}\" data-component-name=\"ButtonCreateButton\"><a class=\"button primary\" href=\"https://framer.link/NEWECONOMIES\"><span>Apply Now</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h4>Why new media is an important trend</h4><p>In the next few years, it&#8217;s unclear whether people will keep reading newsletters at today&#8217;s pace or rely more on AI-generated summaries. </p><p>What&#8217;s clearer is that audio and video will remain strong: because they&#8217;re casual, low-effort ways to consume content, they fit naturally into multitasking and daily routines.</p><p>From our coverage on <a href=\"https://www.neweconomies.co/p/the-creator-economy-2025\">the creator economy</a>, we&#8217;ve seen clear shifts as creators invest in audio and video channels to build closer relationships, diversify revenue, and reach new audiences. </p><p>Podcasts, YouTube, and short-form video have become central to creators building their media empires &#8212; suggesting that while newsletters may evolve alongside AI, audio and video will remain essential formats for connection and growth. </p><p>Brands are also increasingly willing to pay for ad placements throughout creators&#8217; podcasts and videos &#8212; and in some cases, lesser-known brands are paying simply to be featured alongside more notable companies.</p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.neweconomies.co/p/the-new-titans-of-audio\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!eoTD!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F362b1c5f-3935-40bf-851c-ea67147c1d3b_1250x624.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!eoTD!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F362b1c5f-3935-40bf-851c-ea67147c1d3b_1250x624.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!eoTD!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F362b1c5f-3935-40bf-851c-ea67147c1d3b_1250x624.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!eoTD!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F362b1c5f-3935-40bf-851c-ea67147c1d3b_1250x624.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!eoTD!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F362b1c5f-3935-40bf-851c-ea67147c1d3b_1250x624.png\" width=\"1250\" height=\"624\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/362b1c5f-3935-40bf-851c-ea67147c1d3b_1250x624.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:624,&quot;width&quot;:1250,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:74206,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://www.neweconomies.co/p/the-new-titans-of-audio&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topIm